org.rsna.ctp.pipeline

Class AbstractExportService

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.rsna.ctp.pipeline.AbstractPipelineStage
      • org.rsna.ctp.pipeline.AbstractQueuedExportService
        • org.rsna.ctp.pipeline.AbstractExportService
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ExportService, PipelineStage, Scriptable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    AimExportService, DicomExportService, DicomSTOWRSExportService, FtpExportService, FtpsExportService, HttpExportService, SftpExportService

    public abstract class AbstractExportService
extends AbstractQueuedExportService
    An abstract class implementing the ExportService interface. This class provides the queue management and status functions so normal ExportServices only have to receive files and add them to the queue directory.

      • connect

        public Status connect()
        Dummy method which receives notification from the subordinate Exporter Thread that it is about to export files. ExportServices that need to connect to external databases or other systems should override this method.
        Returns:
        indication whether the connection could be made. This method always returns Status.OK, but methods that override it should return the correct result.

      • disconnect

        public Status disconnect()
        Dummy method which receives notification from the subordinate Exporter Thread that it is temporarily done exporting files. ExportServices that need to commit changes to external databases or other systems should override this method.
        Returns:
        indication whether the disconnect processing was successful. This method always returns Status.OK, but methods that override it should return the appropriate result.

        Make an entry in the AuditLog for a successfully transmitted DicomObject.
        Parameters:
        fileObject - the object that was transmitted.
        status - the result of the transmission
        stageName - the name of the sending stage (this.getClass().getName()). If this parameter is null or empty, the name of the sending stage is not logged.
        destination - the URL to which the object was sent.
